BFN 

  [Text] The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song arranged a 
grand banquet for the visiting high-level delegations of 
different countries and delegations of overseas compatriots. 
  The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song, general secretary of 
the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and 
president of the DPRK, arranged a grand banquet at the Kumsusan 
Assembly Hall on 15 April for the visiting high-level 
delegations of different countries and delegations of overseas 
compatriots. 
  When President Kim Il-song, the great leader of our party 
and 
leader, and his wife, accompanied by heads of foreign high-level 
delegations appeared in the banquet hall amid the playing of the 
welcome music, all the participants warmly welcomed him with 
loud applause. 
  Invited to the banquet were the delegation of the National 
Democratic Congress of Ghana headed by General Secretary Huudu 
Yahaya; the delegation of Socialist Party of Kazakhstan headed 
by Co-chairman P.V. Svoik; the delegation of the Workers' Party 
of Ireland headed by General Secretary Pat Quearney; the 
delegation of the Workers' Party of Turkey headed by General 
Secretary Yalsin Buyukdagli; the delegation of the Liaoning 
Provincial Committee of the CPC headed by Secretary Gu Jinchi; 
the delegation of the October 8 Revolutionary Movement of Brazil 
headed by Sergio Rubens, member of the Political Commission and 
secretary of the October 8 Revolutionary Movement of Brazil; 
Maria Lazar, vice president of the Socialist Workers' Party of 
Romania; Vengerovsky, vice chairman of the Liberal Democratic 
Party and deputy speaker of the State Duma of the Federation 
Council of Russia; the delegation of the Khavarovsk Territorial 
Committee and the Amur Regional Committee of the Communist Party 
of the Russian Federation; the delegation of the Japan-Korea 
Friendship Data Center headed by Chairman Oe Yoshiyuki, 
president of the S.B.B. Company, Limited, of Japan; Inoue 
Shuhachi, director general of the International Institute of the 
Chuche Idea; Alexandr Jarikov, secretary general of the World 
Federation of Trade Unions; the delegation of the secretariat of 
the Society for the Study of the Chuche Idea of Japanese 
Teachers, headed by Yokobori Masagazu, adviser and secretary 
general of the Japan Liaison Council of Societies for the Study 
of Kim Chong-il's works; the delegation of the Kim Chong-suk 
Kindergarten in Dalandzadgad City, Omnogov Province, Mongolia; 
the delegation of the Karachi Branch of the Pakistan-Korea 
Friendship Association headed by Abdul Razak Molai; Y.O. Maxim, 
chairman of the Mongolian Study Center of the Chuche Idea; Xu 
Wenbo, vice minister of the PRC Ministry of Culture; Abdul 
Rahman Abdul Farah, vice minister of culture of Egypt; Ssyassi 
Sereyvuth, deputy secretary of state for Ministry of Art of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia; and Ogasawara Mitsuko, head of a delegation 
of the Japan-Korea music and art interchange society. 
  Comrade O Chin-u, member of the presidium of the Political 
Bureau of the WPK Central Committee and minister of the People's 
Armed Forces; Comrade Kang Song-san, member of the Political 
Bureau of the WPK Central Committee and premier of the 
Administration Council; Comrades Yi Chong-ok, Pak Song-chol, and 
Kim Yong-chu, vice presidents and members of the Political 
Bureau of the WPK Central Committee; Vice President Kim 
Pyong-sik, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean 
Social Democratic Party; Comrade Kim Yong-nam, member of the 
Political Bureau of the WPK Central Committee, vice premier of 
the Administration Council, and foreign minister; Comrade Yang 
Hyong-sop, candidate member of the Political Bureau of the WPK 
Central Committee and chairman of the Supreme People's 
Administration; Comrades Kim Chung-nin, Hwang Chang-yop, and Kim 
Yong-sun, secretaries of the WPK Central Committee; Comrades Kim 
Pok-sin, Kim Chang-chu, Kim Yun-hyok, Kim Hwan, and Chang Chol, 
vice premiers of the Administration Council; Comrade Yun Ki-pok, 
chairman of the Economic Policy Committee of the Central 
People's Committee; Comrade Pak Nam-ki, chairman of the 
Pyongyang Municipal Administrative and Economic Committee; Yu 
Mi-yong, chairman of the Chondoist Chongu Party Central 
Committee; Kang Yong-sop, chairman of the Korean Christians 
Federation; Pak Tae-ho, chairman of the Korean Buddhists 
Federation; Chang Chae-chol, chairman of the Korean Roman 
Catholic Association; responsible functionaries of the party, 
power organs, central organs, and public organizations; generals 
of the Korean People's Army; anti-Japanese revolutionary 
fighters; and functionaries concerned were present at the 
banquet. 
  Also present were the congratulatory group of Koreans in 
Japan celebrating 15 April led by Yi Chin-kyu, first vice 
chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan; the delegation of old 
cadres of Chongnyon led by Paek Chong-won, chairman of the 
Sports Federation of Koreans in Japan, and other delegations of 
Chongnyon; Choe Hong-hui, president of the International 
Taekwon-do Federation; and congratulatory groups and overseas 
compatriots from different regions and organizations. 
  The banquet began with the playing of the national anthem. 
  Kang Song-san, member of the Political Bureau of the WPK 
Central Committee and premier of the Administration Council, 
made a speech at the banquet. 
  After this, Huudu Yahaya, general secretary of the National 
Democratic Congress of Ghana, made a speech. 
  Lastly, Yi Chin-kyu, first vice-chairman of the Central 
Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan, also made a speech. 
  The Mansudae Art Troupe gave a performance at the banquet. 
  The banquet proceeded in a warm atmosphere filled with a 
feeling of friendship. 

